# difference between KNN and K means Clustring 

#1.)
# KNN is used for classification and regression 
# K means is used for clustring problems

# 2)
# KNN is supervised algorithm
# K means is unsupervised algorithm

# 3)
# to train KNN ,we need a dataset with all the data
# points having class labels
# for training k means ,we no need such any information

# 4)
# we use KNN  to predict the class label or new points
# we use K means to find patterns in a given data set by grouping data points
# into clusters

error_rate = []
for val in range(1,30):
    knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=val)
    knn.fit(x_train, y_train)
    pred_i = knn.predict(x_test)
    error_rate.append(np.mean(pred_i != y_test))
